Citation.sAbstract: Apparent molar volumes V and apparent molar heat capacities Cp, were determined for aqueous solutions of lead nitrate [Pb(NO3)2] at m=(0.02 to 0.5) mol. kg-1, at T=(278.15 to 393.15) K, and at the pressure 0.35 MPa. Our V values were calculated from densities obtained using a vibrating-tube densimeter, and our Cp, values were obtained using a twin fixed-cell, power-compensation, differential-output, temperature-scanning calorimeter. Our results were fitted to functions of m and T and compared with results from the literature.
Citation.sTitle: Apparent molar volumes and apparent molar heat capacities of aqueous lead nitrate at temperatures from 278.15 K to 393.15 K and at the pressure 0.35 MPa
